### Page 1

PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL Item Management
© Cybersoft SchoolCafé www.schoolcafe.com Page 1 of 12

CREATE POS ONLY ITEMS
The guide will cover how to create POS Only Items, which will create a button to be used on Menu Grids. This includes
entering the recommended information for the POS Item and Allergen Info cards as well as the Images & Docs card. It
will also cover the required information in the POS PRICING tab.
If an Item is intended to be used in Menu Planning or Inventory, see the Create Food Item Quick Guide. The Menu
Info tab will allow users to enable it as a POS Item.
To create POS Only Items, navigate to Item Management > Menu Items.
POS ITEM CARD
The POS Item card contains high-level information for the Menu Item such as the POS Item Name, POS Button Name,
and POS Item Category.
Process / Descriptions Images
On the Menu Items page
1. Click the + NEW button

2. Select POS Only
The Create POS Only Item page displays.

On the Summary card
3. Enter the following information:
• POS Item Name, POS Button Name
(English), and POS Item Category
These fields are required.
• POS Button Name (Spanish), Meal
Type, and Tags
These fields are optional.
• Click the POS Entree checkbox as
needed
The POS Entree option is used to
identify this Menu Item as a reimbursable
meal.
4. Click the SAVE button to continue
The page refreshes, and the POS Item
information is saved.
Once saved, the POS PRICING tab displays.
